      <hedline>
        <hl1>To Vote for Nader, or Not</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Peter Larson letter disputes Robert F Kennedy Jr's August 10 Op-Ed article on threat to environment posed by Green Party presidential candidate Ralph Nader</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Nader's Threat to the Environment,'' by Robert F. Kennedy Jr. (Op-Ed, Aug. 10):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Nader's Threat to the Environment,'' by Robert F. Kennedy Jr. (Op-Ed, Aug. 10):</p>
        <p>Mr. Kennedy may certainly support Al Gore as he chooses, but he shouldn't try to minimize the integrity of my vote for Ralph Nader by calling it a vote for George W. Bush. It is nothing other than a vote for Mr. Nader, regardless of who else may be running.</p>
        <p>Until all voters stand up for their votes as their own reasoned choices, we'll never break the stranglehold of a corrupted two-party system that has recently provided us with two rather uninspiring choices.</p>
        <p>PETER LARSON  Burlington Township, N.J.  Aug. 10, 2000</p>
      </block>
